-- Mail.ru May Offer Subsidiary With Facebook Stake in London IPO, FT Reports
-- B y   C a t h e r i n e   A i r l i e
-- 2010-10-09T08:53:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-09/mail-ru-may-offer-subsidiary-with-facebook-stake-in-london-ipo-ft-reports.html
Mail.ru, the Russian internet portal
formerly known as Digital Sky Technologies Ltd., may float a
business unit that includes a quarter of its 10 percent stake in
Facebook, the social networking website, the Financial Times
 reported , without saying where it got the information.  Mail.ru may offer 25 percent of the subsidiary, also called
Mail.ru, on a London stock exchange, the FT said. The company
may postpone the initial public offer should market conditions
deteriorate, the newspaper said, citing people close to the
company.  To contact the reporter on this story:
